    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> GraionDilach:\n> \n> Sounds like the AI ran out of base space around the MCV. This has nothing to do with Lua.\n> In TS/RA2, there was a property for the AI, that if it cannot place the building in x amount of tries it abandons the production of that one. That should work a ton better compared to your idea, because yours have the danger of deadlocking the AI production queue for unnecessarily long times.\n\nOk let's get picky then.\n\nThis problem was reported a long time ago, since it's not fixed yet I am assuming this problem is requiring too much effort to fix for the devs. So I offered a quick and dirty idea for a fix.\n\nThe key here is RETRY, your idea has the danger of AI abandoning production of everything just because vehicles/people happen to be nearby the base at the wrong time, multiple times.\n\nThe production queue is already \"deadlocking\", it's already rebuilding over and over again, my quick and dirty fix simply tell it to increase the delay between them.\n\n> Unit158 \n> \n> It is not feasable to inteface LuaJIT with our C# code, and it would be extremely dumb to do so even if we could for security reasons.\n\nIn other words, you suck at programming and security.\n\nTell me genius, how smart is it to create a loop that freezes the whole game every few seconds by building the same crap over and over again in an area with little space?\n"
  },
